<!--(From A21) Notes on Positions, rotations, and exits.


	Seat Poses, are sepcific to vehicle and seat number:
	Seaet Poses are pre-made configurations of body placement and position while in a seat.	
	
	Pose 10 means "1 in the 10 is for bicycle" "0 in the 10 means drivers seat" (Vanilla doesn't have passenger seats)
	
	Pose 20 means "2 in the 20 is for motor bike" (There is also pose 21 for the passenger seat)
	
	Pose 30 means "3 in the 30 is for motorcycle" (There is also pose 31 for the passenger seat)
	
	Pose 40 means "4 in the 40 is for truck" (There is pose 41, 42, 43, 44, and 45 for the passenger seats)
	
	Pose 50 means "5 in the 50 is for gyrocopter" (There is pose 51 for the passenger seat)
	
	
	
	Position Theory: While "person" is facing you...
		X Axis - shoulder to shoulder. Increase number, they move to your right.
		Y Axis - Down/Up the spine.	Increase number, they move Up
		Z Axis - Distance, increase number move towards you

		Seat Position Information:
		1st pos, is Left-Right,
		2nd pos, is Up-down, 
		3rd pos, is front-back (Increasing number goes more front, decreasing number goes more back)
		*** +1 to a position moves them 1 meter in appropriate direction. Decimals are allowed.
		
		Seat Rotation Information: (numbers are degrees 0-360)
		The rotation center is NOT in the person, but the 1 meter block it is "standing on"
		the "Center" is the 1 meter block the "person" is standing on.
		So if you were to rotate someone 180 degrees, they are now standing UNDERNEATH that block.
			-To see the person upside down in PLACE, you would have to raise their y axis by 2 meters.
		
		
		1st rot, Spinning on the x-axis. Leaning forward or backwards (increasing number leans more forward)
		2nd rot, Spinning on the y-axis. Facing front, left, right, backwards, etc.
		3rd rot, Spinning on the z-axis. Leaning left, right, upside down, etc.
		(FOR ROTATIONS, using a negative (-) makes the spinning opposite direction)
		
	*POSITIONS WITH FEET AND HANDS WORK DIFFERENTLY*
	HANDS	x Axis - Increase number moves it to your left (while looking at person face to face)
	
		
		
		

	Under "Exit" the "~" means "or". Coordinates given are optional exits in case exits are blocked.
	
	Exit of the gyrocopter gives "left ~ right ~ behind ~ infront ~ above" exit options
	With the truck, similar but to each side.
	
	
				<property name="IKFootLPosition" value="0, 0, 0"/>
				<property name="IKFootLRotation" value="0, 0, 0"/>
				
				<property name="IKFootRPosition" value="0, 0, 0"/>
				<property name="IKFootRRotation" value="0, 0, 0"/>
		
				<property name="IKHandLPosition" value="0, 0, 0"/>
				<property name="IKHandLRotation" value="0, 0, 0"/>	
				
				<property name="IKHandRPosition" value="0, 0, 0"/>
				<property name="IKHandRRotation" value="0, 0, 0"/>
	
	
	
	

-->
